[SPEAKER_12] This is also part of the basis of non-extractive organizations.

539
00:52:33,000 --> 00:52:35,000
[SPEAKER_12] All right.

540
00:52:35,000 --> 00:52:42,000
[SPEAKER_12] Going back to the next discipline of contemplative entrepreneurship is Sabbath and rhythm.

541
00:52:42,000 --> 00:52:52,000
[SPEAKER_12] We think as entrepreneurs that it is essential for us to push through, to force, to always be on the go, go, go, go, right?

542
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:58,000
[SPEAKER_12] You know, and look at people like Jack Dorsey and their crazy schedules and think that we're supposed to be doing the same.

543
00:52:58,000 --> 00:53:00,000
[SPEAKER_12] Not so much.

544
00:53:00,000 --> 00:53:09,000
[SPEAKER_12] So really what we're supposed to be doing as entrepreneurs, you know, the ultimate, you know, basically the ultimate creator, of course, is God, right?

545
00:53:09,000 --> 00:53:13,000
[SPEAKER_12] And if we consider Genesis, the very beginning, right?

546
00:53:13,000 --> 00:53:20,000
[SPEAKER_12] In the beginning, God created for six days and then on the seventh day he rested.

547
00:53:20,000 --> 00:53:28,000
[SPEAKER_12] And if God thinks, you know, if God wants to rest, you know, after six days, then why do we think that we shouldn't be doing the same?

548
00:53:28,000 --> 00:53:33,000
[SPEAKER_12] So we need to honor things like our weekends.

549
00:53:33,000 --> 00:53:40,000
[SPEAKER_12] You know, we need to understand that there's a particular rhythm in our schedules and we need rest.

550
00:53:40,000 --> 00:53:51,000
[SPEAKER_12] It's not just producing, but it is a creative process, you know, entrepreneurship, which means that because it's a creative process, we need to alternate work with rest.

551
00:53:51,000 --> 00:53:52,000
[SPEAKER_12] Okay.

552
00:53:52,000 --> 00:54:08,000
[SPEAKER_12] So basically what this means is not just that we have to find a rhythm on a weekly basis with honoring and respecting our weekends and also the weekends of our employees, but also on a daily basis.

553
00:54:08,000 --> 00:54:12,000
[SPEAKER_12] How can we build a Sabbath into our day, right?

554
00:54:12,000 --> 00:54:16,000
[SPEAKER_12] You know, it could very well be making sure we take time for meals.

555
00:54:16,000 --> 00:54:24,000
[SPEAKER_12] It could be using a Pomodoro timer, you know, to work for 25 minutes, take a five minute break and then do a certain number of Pomodoros and do a longer break.

556
00:54:24,000 --> 00:54:34,000
[SPEAKER_12] But we can find ways of creating this Sabbath rhythm into our day, into our week, into our months, even into our years, you know, periodization with the months.

